The paper proposes a novel objective term for subspace sparse coding (SSC) algorithms to improve clustering results. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with data representation and clustering. The paper also introduces a non-linear local SSC algorithm and a kernel-based framework, which suggests the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) being relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper addresses the issue of redundancies in sparse coding results and proposes a post-processing step to improve the representation graph, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
